2/united states/south carolina/oconee/", "3/united states/south carolina/oconee/walhalla/", "2/united states/south carolina/pickens/", "3/united states/south carolina/pickens/pickens/"], "contributor": ["university of south carolina; columbia, sc"], "date": "1923-09-05", "dates": ["1923-09-05"], "description": ["Jt SOMETHING TO THINK J A no I T 4 Questionnaire is Sent to All South Carol inn Oonjjressiuen and Senators Charlotte X C Herald We are publishing herewith daily press report of questions propounded to South Carolina members of Con gress by Commissioner of Agricul ture I Harris of Columbia S C This is the most important and far reaching questionnaire that has so far emanated from any State official Mr Harris strikes at the very roots of the economic cancer that is eating into the vitals of agriculture and undermining civilization It requires more than ordinary moral courage and honest conviction U prompt a man holding an import ant State office to thus declare him self on the money monopoly as em bodied in the Federal reserve bank ing system and Commissioner Har ris is to be commended for this ac tion The common people and es pecially the farmers of South Caro lina should rally to his support Following is the clipping in full taken from the Daily Observer Declaring that the financial sys tem of the United States must be sweepingly amended in order to guarantee to the agricultural inter ests the protection to which they"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-04-13T08:03:26.445Z", "group": ["ndnp/scu", "university-of-south-carolina-columbia-sc-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84026912/1923-09-05/ed-1/?sp=2", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:scu:batch_scu_kiwi_ver03:data:sn84026912:00542866032:1923090501:0288/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=406&w=284", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:scu:batch_scu_kiwi_ver03:data:sn84026912:00542866032:1923090501:0288/full/pct